To display the online users' list on your website, you will need to use a combination of backend and frontend technologies.

On the backend, you need to query the database to find the list of online users. Once you have the list, you can create an API endpoint that returns this data in a format that is consumable by the frontend.

On the frontend, you can use JavaScript to make an API call to the endpoint you created on the backend. You can use a library like Axios to make the API call and retrieve the data. Once you have the data, you can use HTML and CSS to display the list of online users on the webpage.

Here are the high-level steps you can follow:

1. Query the database to find the list of online users.
2. Create an API endpoint on the backend that returns this data.
3. Use JavaScript to make an API call to the endpoint.
4. Use HTML and CSS to display the list of online users on the webpage.

